<p><img src="1.jpg" alt="umatter" /></p>

<p>I am an Assistant Professor of Economics at the University of St. Gallenâ€™s <a href="https://www.unisg.ch/en/universitaet/schools/economics-and-political-science/ueber-seps" target="_blank">SEPS-HSG</a>. My primary research interests lie at the intersection of data science, quantitative political economics, and online media economics.</p>

<p>I am PI for the SNSF Grant on <a href="https://data.snf.ch/grants/grant/207698">Consequences of Personalized Information Provision Online: Segregation, Polarization, and Radicalization (2022-2026)</a> and
the SNSF Grant on <a href="https://data.snf.ch/grants/grant/215523">Ideological Ad Targeting in Consumer Markets and the Political Market Place (2023-2027)</a>.</p>

<p>In addition to my research activities, I have designed several new courses at the intersection of data science and applied econometrics (<a href="courses/bigdata/bigdata_factsheet.pdf" target="_blank">Big Data Analytics</a>, <a href="courses/webmining/webmining_factsheet.pdf" target="_blank">Introduction to Web Mining</a>, <a href="courses/datahandling/datahandling_factsheet.pdf" target="_blank">Data Handling</a>) and have been honored for excellence in teaching at the school and university level.</p>

<p>Before joining the University of St. Gallen, I was a Visiting Researcher at the <a href="http://cyber.harvard.edu" target="_blank">Berkman Klein Center for Internet &amp; Society at Harvard University</a>.</p>


